The paper presents a randomized algorithm for computing the minimal-norm solution to an underdetermined system of linear equations, which involves numerical analysis (cs.NA) and optimization (cs.DS). The algorithm's performance is evaluated using numerical examples, which suggests that it may fall under machine learning (cs.LG) or signal processing (cs.IT). Finally, the paper's focus on computational efficiency and performance suggests that it may also belong to scientific computing (cs.SI).
